The paper discusses the use of convolutional low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of potential functions, which are commonly used in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper's focus on joint decoding of LDPC codes suggests a connection to network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's use of density-evolution equations suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
